[{"id":"VR152692","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR152618.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">For a population to be in Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium, certain conditions must be met. Which of the following best explains a characteristic of the fly populations that meets a condition of Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR152692_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of an experiment involving a population of fruit flies. At the top of the diagram, a sealed chamber labeled “Initial Population of Fruit Flies” contains a population of fruit flies and a nutrient medium. Below this, arrows branch off to indicate that the initial population is separated into two groups, where each group contains four sealed chambers of fruit flies and one of two types of nutrient medium. The four chambers on the left are labeled “Group 1, Grown on Starch.” The four chambers on the right are labeled “Group 2, Grown on Maltose.” At the bottom of the diagram, an arrow from Group 1 and an arrow from Group 2 converge and point to a pair of fruit flies, one male and one female, with an “X” between them to indicate the opportunity to mate.\" height=\"308\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR152618.g03.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">Figure 1. Experimental steps taken to determine whether the nutrient source in a growth chamber affects mating preference</p>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">A population of fruit flies (<span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Drosophila pseudoobscura</span>) grown on a typical nutrient source was separated into several growth chambers. Each of the new chambers was assigned a different source of carbohydrates for nutrition, either starch or maltose, and maintained for many generations (Figure 1).</p>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">After a year, male and female flies were paired up in different combinations. The instances of mating between the males and females grown on the same nutrient source and males and females grown on different nutrient sources were recorded (Table 1).</p>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:1 frame:none pgwide:1\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colwidth:400\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col1\">\n\t\t\t<p class=\"text-center\">TABLE 1. MATING INSTANCES BETWEEN MALES AND FEMALES GROWN ON</p>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"formatted_line_break delivery_mode:Both text-center\"></span>\n\n\t\t\t<p class=\"text-center\">THE SAME OR DIFFERENT NUTRIENT SOURCES</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup cols:3 pgwide:1\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colwidth:115\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:120\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:125\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\">Females Grown on Starch</td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\">Females Grown on Maltose</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">Males Grown on Starch</td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"22\"><math alttext=\"22\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>22</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"9\"><math alttext=\"9\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">Males Grown on Maltose</td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"8\"><math alttext=\"8\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"20\"><math alttext=\"20\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>20</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">To test whether the mating preferences were simply the result of being isolated in separate growth chambers, the researchers tested the mating preferences of flies that were both grown on starch, but in either the same or different chambers (Table 2).</p>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:1 frame:none pgwide:1\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colwidth:400\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col1\">TABLE 2. MATING INSTANCES BETWEEN MALES AND FEMALES GROWN ON THE SAME NUTRIENT SOURCE IN THE SAME OR DIFFERENT CHAMBERS</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup cols:3 pgwide:1\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colwidth:115\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:125\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:125\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\">Females Grown on Starch in Chamber <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\">Females Grown on Starch in Chamber <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">Males Grown on Starch in Chamber <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"18\"><math alttext=\"18\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>18</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"15\"><math alttext=\"15\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>15</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td align=\"justify\" class=\"entry colname:col1\" valign=\"middle\">Males Grown on Starch in Chamber <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col2\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"12\"><math alttext=\"12\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td align=\"center\" class=\"entry colname:col3\" valign=\"middle\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"15\"><math alttext=\"15\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>15</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The population size of the flies was very small, which increases the likelihood of random mutations having a greater impact.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Since the flies were confined in chambers, they did not experience any migration, so no new alleles were introduced through migration.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Flies have a relatively short generation time and therefore are more likely to pass mutations to the next generation.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The different food sources may have exerted selective pressure on the fly populations, giving an advantage to certain flies.</p>"],"answer":1}]